-- my-ds.page: 👈🏻 TOC Sidebar

Like `navbar` `sidebar` is also inbuilt component of `doc-site`.  Just using
`page` sidebar will appear on your page.

👈🏻 TOC Sidebar uses `fastn.sitemap` which can be added insite your `FASTN.ftd`
file. 

To learn more how to implement `fast.sitemap` go through this 
[video tutorial](https://fastn.com/clean-urls/-/build/).

⭐ Creating a sidebar is useful to:

- Group multiple **related pages**
- **Display a sidebar** on each page







-- end: my-ds.page